prompt:
http://www.usa.gov/citizens/holidays.shtml

What webpage is this URL likely to show?
feedback: When you look at a URL, looking at the beginning should give you some clues about what site you’re on. This web page is on www.usa.gov … The dot-gov means this is a government website, and “USA” should give you a clue that it’s the United States government. The next part of the URL is “citizens.” That probably means this information is for U.S. citizens--but that’s pretty general information. The last part of the URL is “holidays.shtml” so the page is probably about holidays. All the answer choices are about holidays, but the only one that’s likely on a U.S. government website is information about commonly celebrated U.S. holidays. That’s the best answer.
